-- PRESS DIGEST - Hong Kong - Aug 12
-- By Donny Kwok
-- Mon Aug 11, 2014 09:46PM EDT
-- None



HONG KONG, Aug 12 (Reuters) - These are some of the leading stories in Hong Kong newspapers on Tuesday. Reuters has not verified these stories and does not vouch for their accuracy.

SOUTH CHINA MORNING POST  -- An exhibition on the life of Deng Xiaoping, which is to be held in Hong Kong's Convention and Exhibition Centre from Aug. 21-23, may touch on the June 4 incident, according to the event organiser Gao Yi, deputy secretary general of the Communist Party Central Committee's Party Literature Research Office. (http://bit.ly/1sS5BWT) -- The Hong Kong Monetary Authority will put greater effort into promoting the city's fund and wealth management industry in the next five years, said its chairman Norman Chan Tak-lam. (http://bit.ly/1oYWMd7)  THE STANDARD -- The delay in building the long-awaited high-speed rail link will cost an additional HK$6.5 billion ($838.6 million), taking the total cost to HK$71.5 billion. The Hong Kong government warned it might claim for damages for breach of its agreement with MTR Corp <0066.HK>. (http://bit.ly/1ul1upj) -- SmarTone Telecommunications <0315.HK> is to raise the monthly fee of its lowest priced 3G plan to HK$90 from HK$80. Among local operators, only China Mobile Hong Kong <0941.HK> and China Unicom Hong Kong <0762.HK> have not hiked prices of their cheapest monthly service plans, which are still at HK$80. (http://bit.ly/1oF3osD) -- Mobile game developer IGG <8002.HK> plans to launch up to 25 new games this year. IGG plans to launch five games by September. Four of the titles were developed in-house and one is licensed from a third party. (http://bit.ly/1oYZcIL)  HONG KONG ECONOMIC JOURNAL  -- Texhong Textile Group <2678.HK> has held back its production expansion plan in Vietnam due to the uncertain political situation in the country, according to chairman Hong Tianzhu. -- Menswear brand China LiLang Ltd <1234.HK>, which posted a 0.2 percent decline in first-half turnover, expects to see growth in its full year turnover with low-single-digit growth in same store sales in the second half of the year.   APPLE DAILY -- Sinopec Corp <0386.HK><600028.SS> chairman Fu Chengyu  held a meeting with Tencent <0700.HK> president Lau Chi Ping on potential cooperation in the future, Sinopec's parent China Petrochemical Corp said on its website.